<disp-formula id="M3"><label>3</label><graphic xlink:href="gkp752m3"/></disp-formula>
where <italic>L<sub>h</sub></italic> is a model for linker regions analyzed by a hydrophobicity index <italic>h</italic>, which is one of {KD, WW, HH}, and <italic>R<sub>h</sub></italic> is a model for random sequences. The maximum probability among the three ones computed using three different hydrophobicity indices was defined as the final emission probability for the hidden states of the linker region (<xref ref-type="fig" rid="F3">Figure 3</xref>).
